#   -h / --help          (auto-injected by AP_PARSER)
#
# gecop ("Gobo Eiffel Cop") is an Eiffel language
# conformance validation suite — runs a test suite
# against various Eiffel compilers (gec, gelint,
# ise/EiffelStudio, etc.) and reports compatibility.
# Authored by Eric Bezault as part of the Gobo
# Eiffel Project (62 GH stars).  Sister tools: gec
# (Gobo Eiffel Compiler, in corpus as `_gec`),
# gecc (Gobo Eiffel C Compilation, DEFERRED for
# separate round), gedoc (Gobo Eiffel
# Documentation generator, DEFERRED), gelint
# (Gobo Eiffel Lint, DEFERRED), gepp (Gobo Eiffel
# Preprocessor, DEFERRED).  Multi-binary Gobo
# toolchain offers 4+ future R-rounds.
#
# Critical extraction note: gecop uses **Gobo
# Eiffel `AP_PARSER` library** at gecop.e:528 +
# the entire spec block — corpus's **first
# documented Eiffel CLI library**.  Gobo
# Argument Parser library (library/argument/) is
# part of the Gobo Eiffel Project (62 GH stars,
# Eric Bezault et al, 2006-2018), the most-used
# Eiffel third-party libraries collection.
# Distinct from raw `ARGUMENTS_32` Eiffel stdlib
# class (just provides `argument_count` +
# `argument(I)` accessors; no parser — caller
# writes manual matching), and from EiffelBase's
# `KL_ARGUMENT_LIST` (also low-level access).
# Gobo AP_PARSER adds: typed option classes
# (`AP_FLAG`/`AP_STRING_OPTION`/`AP_INTEGER_OPTION`/
# `AP_BOOLEAN_OPTION`), enum-restriction via
# `.extend(VALUE)`, alternative-options-lists for
# mutex, automatic help generation.  Extends cross-
# language CLI taxonomy to FIFTY-FOUR library
# variants: Rust (6), Go (4), Python (3),
# Crystal 1 OptionParser (R269), Haskell (R270),
# OCaml (R271), C (R272), Java (R276),
# Kotlin (R277), Scala (R278), Dart (R279),
# Ruby (R280), Perl (R281), PHP (R282),
# Swift (R283), F# (R284), Lua (R285), C# (R286),
# Nim 1 parseopt (R287), Zig (R288), D (R289),
# Racket (R290), Common Lisp 1 (R291),
# Erlang (R292), Tcl (R293), Pharo Smalltalk (R294),
# Common Lisp 2 clingon (R295), Julia (R296),
# SWI-Prolog optparse (R297), Pony stdlib cli (R298),
# Crystal 2 Admiral (R299), V stdlib `flag` (R300),
# Nim 2 cligen (R301), Clojure babashka.cli (R302),
# Gleam Glint (R303), Ada GNAT.Command_Line (R304),
# C++ CLI11 (R305), Elixir Optimus (R306), Vala
# GLib.OptionContext (R307), Hare stdlib getopt
# (R308), Standard ML stdlib GetOpt (R309),
# Fortran M_CLI2 (R310), Guile (ice-9 getopt-long)
# (R311), Free Pascal TCustomApplication (R312),
# Idris 2 System.GetOpts (R313), Mercury stdlib
# getopt_io (R314), **Eiffel Gobo AP_PARSER**
# (R315 — NEW).  **MAJOR PATTERN MILESTONE**: 54
# cross-language CLI library variants documented.
#
# Critical extraction note: gecop uses **Eiffel
# multiple-inheritance-with-feature-export-
# controls CLI pattern** at gecop.e:11-25 —
# `inherit UT_GOBO_CLI, KL_SHARED_EXCEPTIONS, ...`.
# Eiffel supports MULTIPLE INHERITANCE with
# explicit feature-level EXPORT STATUS control
# (`export {NONE} all end` hides all inherited
# features from clients).  Distinct from R312
# Pascal `class(TCustomApplication)` (single
# inheritance), R305 C++ CLI11 (no inheritance —
# composition), R313 Idris 2 (no inheritance).
# Eiffel's approach: MULTIPLE INHERITANCE WITH
# EXPORT CONTROL — corpus's **first documented
# multiple-inheritance-with-export-controls CLI
# pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: gecop uses **Eiffel
# Design-by-Contract preconditions in CLI parse
# routine** at gecop.e:528-535 — `require
# a_args_not_void: a_args /= Void no_void_arg:
# across a_args as i_arg all i_arg /= Void end`
# uses Eiffel's UNIQUE DESIGN-BY-CONTRACT
# mechanism.  `require` block introduces named
# preconditions; each is a typed assertion that
# the COMPILER checks (compile-time) AND the
# RUNTIME verifies (when assertions are enabled).
# Distinct from EVERY other CLI library in the
# corpus — Eiffel is the ONLY language with built-
# in Design-by-Contract (Bertrand Meyer, 1985).
# Sister features: `ensure` postconditions,
# `invariant` class invariants, `check` inline
# assertions.  Corpus's **first documented Design-
# by-Contract CLI pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: gecop uses **Gobo
# `AP_STRING_OPTION.extend(VALUE)` for ENUM
# allowed values** at gecop.e:541-548 — `tool_
# option.extend("ge")` / `.extend("ise")` /
# `.extend("gec")` etc. add ALLOWED VALUES to the
# option.  The parser will REJECT values not in
# the enum.  Distinct from R295 CL clingon
# `:option-type :choice :choices '("a" "b")`
# (constructor kwarg), R305 C++ CLI11 `->check(
# CLI::IsMember(set))` (validator method), R301
# Nim cligen (no enum restriction at spec time).
# Gobo's approach: METHOD-CHAIN EXTEND for ENUM —
# corpus's **first documented extend-for-enum CLI
# pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: gecop uses **Eiffel
# `'V'` single-quote char-literal short flag**
# at gecop.e:589 — `create version_flag.make
# ('V', "version")`.  AP_FLAG's creation
# procedure takes `(SHORT_CHAR, LONG_STR)`.
# Eiffel uses SINGLE QUOTES for CHARACTER LITERALS
# (like C, Pony, Hare).  Sister to R291 CL `#\h`,
# R292 Erlang `$h`, R298 Pony `'p'`, R300 V
# `` `n` ``, R308 Hare `'1'`, R311 Guile `#\X`.
# **EIGHTH character-literal CLI cluster language**:
# CL `#\X` (R291, R295), Erlang `$X` (R292),
# Pony `'X'` (R298), V `` `X` `` (R300), Hare
# `'X'` (R308), Guile `#\X` (R311), **Eiffel
# `'X'`** (R315 — NEW).  Corpus's **eighth
# character-literal CLI cluster language**.
#
# Critical extraction note: gecop uses **Gobo
# `AP_ALTERNATIVE_OPTIONS_LIST` for mutex
# options** at gecop.e:591-592 — `create l_list.
# make (version_flag) l_parser.alternative_
# options_lists.force_last (l_list)`.  AP_
# ALTERNATIVE_OPTIONS_LIST is a Gobo-specific
# SET OF OPTIONS where ONLY ONE may be specified
# at a time (mutual exclusion).  When `-V` is
# specified, OTHER options in the same list
# become INVALID.  Distinct from R301 Nim cligen
# (no built-in mutex), R302 Clojure babashka.cli
# (no mutex), R303 Gleam Glint (no mutex), R305
# C++ CLI11 `->excludes(...)` method, R306
# Elixir Optimus (no mutex).  Gobo's approach:
# ALTERNATIVE-OPTIONS-LIST as a FIRST-CLASS
# structure — corpus's **first documented
# alternative-options-list-as-first-class CLI
# pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: gecop uses **Eiffel
# instantiate-configure-append option-spec
# pattern** at gecop.e:538 et seq — each option
# is INSTANTIATED with `create OPT.make_with_
# long_form (NAME)`, CONFIGURED via setter calls
# (`set_description`, `set_parameter_description`,
# `extend`), then APPENDED to the parser's
# option list with `l_parser.options.force_last
# (OPT)`.  Distinct from R301 Nim cligen (proc-
# signature spec — no append), R302 Clojure
# babashka.cli (vector of maps constructed at
# once), R307 Vala GLib (struct-literal table
# built statically), R310 Fortran M_CLI2 (single-
# string-packed spec).  Gobo's approach:
# INSTANTIATE-CONFIGURE-APPEND — each option is
# BUILT UP STEP-BY-STEP before registration.
# Corpus's **first documented instantiate-
# configure-append CLI pattern**.
#
# Hunt-skip notes: skipped `_gec` (Gobo Eiffel
# Compiler, already in corpus + blacklisted —
# uses AP_PARSER but ~50+ option surface), `_alr`
# (Ada package manager, not Eiffel), `_unison`
# (DUP with stock zsh).  Probed `simple-eiffel/
# simple_graphviz` (0 stars — uses MANUAL
# argument-parsing via ARGUMENTS_32, NOT a CLI
# library; deferred for handwritten-parser-
# pattern round), `oligot/epm` (Eiffel Package
# Manager — uses AP_PARSER but only 1 subcommand
# 'sync' — smaller surface than gecop),
# `EiffelWebFramework/EWF gewf` (46 stars but
# framework-internal, less standalone), `gobo-
# eiffel/gobo gecc` (Gobo Eiffel C Compilation —
# 2-option surface, sister to gecop; DEFERRED for
# separate round), `gobo-eiffel/gobo gedoc` (Gobo
# Eiffel Doc generator — sister tool; DEFERRED),
# `gobo-eiffel/gobo gelint` (Eiffel linter; sister
# tool, DEFERRED), `imustafin/brie_doom` (11
# stars — DOOM source port; specialized).  Chose
# gecop: 10 options + version flag in a single
# 600-line gecop.e (real conformance-test driver
# distributed with Gobo Eiffel), exercises EVERY
# MAJOR Gobo AP_PARSER PATTERN (multiple
# inheritance with UT_GOBO_CLI, multiple creation
# procedures, DBC preconditions, AP_STRING_OPTION/
# AP_INTEGER_OPTION/AP_FLAG typed option classes,
# `make_with_long_form` constructor, `.extend()`
# for enum values, `'V'` Eiffel char-literal short
# flag, AP_ALTERNATIVE_OPTIONS_LIST for mutex,
# `l_parser.options.force_last` registration,
# `parse_array` parse invocation, `was_found`
# boolean accessor), real binary distributed via
# Gobo's installer + brew/AUR packages.  Sister
# Gobo tools provide 3+ future R-rounds.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

# Eiffel tool enum from tool_option.extend() calls
# at gecop.e:541-548
local -a gecop_tools=(
  'ge:Gobo Eiffel compiler (default)'
  'ise:ISE EiffelStudio compiler'
  'gec:Gobo Eiffel C compiler driver'
  'gelint:Gobo Eiffel Lint'
  'ge_debug:Gobo Eiffel compiler debug build'
  'ge_lint:Gobo Eiffel Lint debug build'
  'ise_debug:ISE EiffelStudio debug build'
  'ise_dotnet:ISE EiffelStudio .NET build'
  'ise_dotnet_debug:ISE EiffelStudio .NET debug build'
)

# 10 options decoded source-direct from gecop.e:535-589
_arguments -s -S \
  '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[display Gobo AP_PARSER auto-generated help]' \
  '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print the version number of gecop and exit]' \
  '--tool=[Eiffel tool to be tested (default: ge)]:tool:->tools' \
  '--tool-executable=[executable filename of Eiffel tool to be tested]:filename:_command_names -e' \
  '--validation=[directory containing the Eiffel validation suite]:directory_name:_files -/' \
  '--filter=[run only test cases matching this regexp]:regexp:' \
  '--aggregate=[aggregate test results into a single report (default: yes)]:no|yes:(no yes)' \
  '--diff=[compare test results with the previous run (default: yes)]:no|yes:(no yes)' \
  '--keep-testdir[do not delete temporary directory after running the validation suite]' \
  '--thread=[number of threads (negative N means "CPUs - N"; default: -3)]:thread_count:' \
  '--progress[display progress status during execution of the validation suite]' && ret=0

case $state in
  tools)
    _describe -t eiffel_tools 'Eiffel tool' gecop_tools && ret=0
    ;;
esac

return ret
